It would be great if the [Space List macro|http://confluence.atlassian.com/x/byAC] had a parameter for _labels_ so that users could only list spaces that had a particular label.

This may go some way to help solve this [feature request|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-1095] for nested spaces as users could add multiple space lists to their dashboard each with a different label filter.

To replicate:
 - Go to Global Templates, and create a template containing:
{noformat}
h1. Test livesearch for @PROJ@
{livesearch}
{noformat}
 - Create a page using this template.
After being prompted for the variable, Confluence returns to the edit page. But now you'll notice that the "Location" field is blank. Saving the page results in a "Page Not Found" error.

